cas (Dorset), Sandford, Sampford Courtney, Sampford Peverell, and Sampford Spiney (all Devon), Sampford Arundel and Sampford Brett (both Somerset), and Sandford (Shropshire). See also   Sandiford  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Samford","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sanderford","meanings":["English: variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sanford","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sandiford","meanings":["English (Lancashire): variant of   Sandifer  ."]}]},{"name":"Gamel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Fanciful spelling of   Gail  , also occasionally written  <b>Gaelle</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gail","meanings":["Shortened form of   Abigail .  It was not found as an independent given name before the middle of the 20th century; it became popular in the 1950s and 1960s, but has since fallen out of fashion."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gamel de Sandford was born about 1070, in Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Sanford, was 31 and his mother, Mrs Thomas de Sandford, was 28. He married Mrs. Gamel de Sandford about 1099, in Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1125, in Bad Aibling, Bavaria, Germany, at the age of 56."},"et":{"ABT 1070–1125":"umbes 1070–1125","1070–1085":"1070–1085","1070–1125":"1070–1125","1076–Male":"1076–Surnud","1096–Male":"1096–Surnud","1082–Female":"1082–Surnud","1100–1186":"1100–1186","1040–1104":"1040–1104","1044–Femal